## P0 — Must Do (Highest Impact)

### 1. 🖥️ Live Visual Renderer (Web UI)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **This is the single highest-impact improvement.** Judges will open your Space and see a real-time animation of the robot navigating, picking up parts, and delivering them. First impressions win hackathons.

**What**: A browser-based grid visualization served at the root `/` URL of the HuggingFace Space.

**Spec**:
- HTML/CSS/JS page served by the existing FastAPI server
- Connects via WebSocket to watch live agent runs
- Shows:
  - Color-coded grid (walls=gray, hazards=red, pickups=green, dropoffs=blue, robot=yellow)
  - Robot position animated in real-time
  - Current carrying status, step count, reward
  - Delivery progress bar
  - LLM thought bubble showing AI reasoning
- "Run Demo" button that triggers inference for a selected difficulty
- Responsive layout (judges may view on different screens)

**Cell Color Scheme**:
```
Empty   = #1a1a2e (dark background)
Wall    = #4a4a5a (gray blocks)
Hazard  = #ff4757 (red glow)
Pickup  = #2ed573 (green pulse)
Dropoff = #1e90ff (blue pulse)
Conveyor= #ffa502 (orange arrows)
Robot   = #ffdd57 (yellow, animated)
```

**Architecture**:
```
Browser ──WebSocket──> FastAPI /ws/viewer
                        │
                        ├── receives grid state updates
                        ├── receives AI thought text
                        └── renders animated grid
```

**Files to create/modify**:
